  "tips": [
    {
      "type": "lead",
      "text": "Typing a sharp reply fast means the words come out as fast as you think them. Loop each one until it is automatic. No new keys here, just flow. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "drop",
      "text": "Hands on home row, eyes off the keys. Repeat each word at one even pace - same gap between every tap. Don't rush to fire back, keep the beat steady."
    },
    {
      "type": "callout",
      "icon": "🎶",
      "title": "Even beat",
      "text": "Pick a tempo you can hold and stay in it. Smooth and even beats fast and jerky every time - a steady hand makes the better point. Let the rhythm carry you."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "point point point point point",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "Rhythm: point",
      "hint": "Loop it on the beat: point - point - point. Same gap every time."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "agree agree agree agree",
      "finger": "pink",
      "title": "Rhythm: agree",
      "hint": "Hold the tempo: agree - agree - agree. Flow, not force."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "kind": "drill",
      "target": "think think think think",
      "finger": "blue",
      "title": "Rhythm: think",
      "hint": "Stay even to the end: think - think - think. Don't rush the finish."
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "text": "Feel the whole word landing in one smooth move? That is the point - even reps turn thinking into reflex, so your fingers can keep up with your argument instead of holding it back."
    },
    {
